ing awareness, and building something real.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>What Happens Next?</div><div><br></div><div>The Find Ivory Fund is officially discontinued.</div><div><br></div><div>All videos promoting the $1,000 reward are being deleted.</div><div><br></div><div>The focus is now 100% on the Emergence Party and its mission.</div><div><br></div><div>My advertising budget will now go toward spreading awareness, engaging with voters, and ensuring the Emergence Party gets the recognition it deserves.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div>A New Path Forward</div><div><br></div><div>This decision feels right. Instead of chasing Ivory, I am building something that will naturally draw the right people to me. If she is meant to be part of my journey, she will find me through this movement, not because of a monetary reward.</div><div><br></div><div>For those who were invested in the Find Ivory Fund‚Äîthank you for your support. Now, I invite you to stand behind something even bigger. Let‚Äôs build a movement that changes Australia for the better.</div><div><br></div><div>If you believe in the Emergence Party, if you want to see a new kind of leadership in Australia, and if you want to be part of a movement that challenges the status quo, then I ask you to join me.</div><div><br></div><div>üîó Support the Emergence Party at wendellsdiary.com</div>
